Dauren Kunanbayev has resigned as COO of uranium major Kazatomprom, the London-listed company announced on Wednesday. Aliya Akzholova, currently director of the mining department at Kazatomprom, would be acting as interim COO, while the internal and board processes were undertaken to appoint a new COO. "We respect Mr. Kunanbayev's decision to leave the company, thank him for his contributions to Kazatomprom's development, and wish him all the best in his future endeavours," said CEO Galymzhan Pirmatov.